Package: NMAR
Type: Package
Title: Estimation under Not Missing at Random Nonresponse
Version: 0.0.0.1
Maintainer: Maciej Beręsewicz <Maciej.Beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl>
Author: Maciej Beręsewicz [aut, cre],
    Igor Kołodziej [aut],
    Mateusz Iwaniuk [aut]
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maciej", "Beręsewicz", email = "Maciej.Beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Igor", "Kołodziej", email = "igor.kolodziej@proton.me", role = "aut"),
    person("Mateusz", "Iwaniuk", email = "mateusz.iwaniuk11@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Description: Provides estimation tools for finite-population parameters when
    outcomes are subject to nonignorable (Not Missing at Random, NMAR)
    nonresponse. Methods can incorporate auxiliary information and
    user-specified response models, and support independent samples as well as
    complex survey designs via objects from the 'survey' package. Returns
    diagnostics and optional variance estimates.
